     1→//! Baseline metrics tracking and regression detection
     2→//!
     3→//! This module implements automated baseline calculation and comparison
     4→//! for autopilot metrics. It enables tracking of performance over time
     5→//! and automatic detection of regressions.
     6→//!
     7→//! # CLI Commands
     8→//!
     9→//! ```bash
    10→//! # Update baselines from recent sessions (last 100 by default)
    11→//! cargo autopilot metrics baseline update
    12→//!
    13→//! # Update with custom session count
    14→//! cargo autopilot metrics baseline update --sessions 200
    15→//!
    16→//! # Show current baselines
    17→//! cargo autopilot metrics baseline show
    18→//!
    19→//! # Show as JSON
    20→//! cargo autopilot metrics baseline show --format json
    21→//!
    22→//! # Check for regressions
    23→//! cargo autopilot metrics baseline check
    24→//!
    25→//! # Generate baseline report
    26→//! cargo autopilot metrics baseline report
    27→//! ```
    28→//!
    29→//! # Automated Updates
    30→//!
    31→//! Baselines can be updated automatically:
    32→//! - Via CLI: `cargo autopilot metrics baseline update`
    33→//! - Via API: `BaselineCalculator::update_all_baselines()`
    34→//! - Schedule weekly updates with cron or systemd timer
    35→//!
    36→//! # Baseline History
    37→//!
    38→//! Baselines are versioned by timestamp in the `updated_at` field.
    39→//! Historical tracking can detect performance trends over time.
    40→//! The database maintains one current baseline per dimension.
    41→
    42→use anyhow::Result;
    43→use chrono::Utc;
    44→use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
    45→use std::collections::HashMap;
    46→
    47→use super::{Baseline, MetricsDb, SessionMetrics};
